lead_paragraph: Keyora Wharry and Jamie Patrick scored 15 points each and No. 25 Colorado State clinched at least a share of the Mountain West Conference regular-season title and extended its school-record win streak to 23 straight with a 74-56 victory over Nevada on Saturday.

headline.print_headline: No. 25 Colorado State Women Win 74-56, Run Win Streak to 23
